claim.claim-text:
An electric power steering apparatus (1) comprising:
a motor (10) for generating steering assist power;
a torque sensor (22) for detecting steering torque (T) of a steering wheel (2);
a sensor (24) for detecting vehicle velocity (V);
means (41) for storing a correspondence relationship between the steering torque (T) and basic assist torque (To); and
means (20) for controlling said motor (10) so that the steering assist power is generated according to the basic assist torque (To) corresponding to the detected steering torque (T) and the detected vehicle velocity,
characterized in that
said electric power steering apparatus (1) further comprises:
means (20) for storing a correspondence relationship between the detected steering torque (T) and the basic assist torque (To) being set such that an assist gradient (R) that is a rate of change of the basic assist torque (To) to the steering torque (T) varies according to variation of the steering torque (T);
means (20a) for determining the assist gradient (R) corresponding to the detected steering torque (T);
a low-pass filter (61) for removing a high-frequency component from an output signal of said torque sensor (22);
assist gradient response phase lead compensation means (63) for advancing phase of the output signal of said torque sensor (22) that passes through said low-pass filter (61) according to the decrease of the determined assist gradient (R);
means (31) for determining a rotation angular velocity corresponding value that corresponds to an angular velocity (dθh/dt, dθm/dt) of rotation determined by differential of a steering angle (θh) of said steering wheel (2) detected by a steering angle sensor (23) or a rotation angle (θm) of said motor (10) detected by an angle sensor (27);
means (31) for storing a correspondence relationship between said rotation angular velocity corresponding value and a correction basic current (ia) that is in inverse correlation with this rotation angular velocity corresponding value; and
means (20) for correcting the output of the motor (10) according to the correction basic current (ia) corresponding to the determined rotation angular velocity corresponding value, whereby
a correction amount of the output of the motor (10) is varied according to the variation of the assist gradient (R).

An electric power steering apparatus (1) comprising:
a motor (10) for generating steering assist power;
a torque sensor (22) for detecting steering torque (T) of a steering wheel (2);
a sensor (24) for detecting vehicle velocity (V);
means (41) for storing a correspondence relationship between the steering torque (T) and basic assist torque (To); and
means (20) for controlling said motor (10) so that the steering assist power is generated according to the basic assist torque (To) corresponding to the detected steering torque (T) and the detected vehicle velocity,
characterized in that
said electric power steering apparatus (1) further comprises:
means (20) for storing a correspondence relationship between the detected steering torque (T) and the basic assist torque (To) being set such that an assist gradient (R) that is a rate of change of the basic assist torque (To) to the steering torque (T) varies according to variation of the steering torque (T);
means (20a) for determining the assist gradient (R) corresponding to the detected steering torque (T);
a low-pass filter (61) for removing a high-frequency component from an output signal of said torque sensor (22);
assist gradient response phase lag compensation means (65) for delaying phase of the output signal of said torque sensor (22) that passes through said low-pass filter (61) according to increase of the determined assist gradient (R);
means (31) for determining a rotation angular velocity corresponding value that corresponds to an angular velocity (dθh/dt, dθm/dt) of rotation determined by differential of a steering angle (θh) of said steering wheel (2) detected by a steering angle sensor (23) or a rotation angle (θm) of said motor (10) detected by an angle sensor (27);
means (31) for storing a correspondence relationship between said rotation angular velocity corresponding value and a correction basic current (ia) that is in inverse correlation with this rotation angular velocity corresponding value; and
means (20) for correcting the output of the motor (10) according to the correction basic current (ia) corresponding to the determined rotation angular velocity corresponding value, whereby
a correction amount of the output of the motor (10) is varied according to the variation of the assist gradient (R).

An electric power steering apparatus (1) comprising:
a motor (10) for generating steering assist power;
a torque sensor (22) for detecting steering torque (T) of a steering wheel (2);
a sensor (24) for detecting vehicle velocity (V);
means (41) for storing a correspondence relationship between the steering torque (T) and basic assist torque (To); and
means (20) for controlling said motor (10) so that the steering assist power is generated according to the basic assist torque (To) corresponding to the detected steering torque (T) and the detected vehicle velocity,
characterized in that
said electric power steering apparatus (1) further comprises:
means (20) for storing a correspondence relationship between the detected steering torque (T) and the basic assist torque (To) being set such that an assist gradient (R) that is a rate of change of the basic assist torque (To) to the steering torque (T) varies according to variation of the steering torque (T);
an upper limit value (Ro) is set for the assist gradient (R) that varies according to variation of the steering torque (T), and the correspondence relationship between the steering torque (T) and the basic assist torque (To) is set such that the set upper limit value (Ro) of the assist gradient (R) varies according to variation of vehicle velocity (V);
means (20a) for determining the set upper limit value (Ro) of the assist gradient (R) at the detected vehicle velocity (V);
a low-pass filter (61) for removing a high-frequency component from an output signal of said torque sensor (22); and
assist gradient response phase compensation means (71) for performing phase lead-lag compensation for the output signal of said torque sensor (22) that passes through said low-pass filter (61) in such a manner that a frequency of an end point of the phase lead and a frequency of a start point of the phase lag vary according to the set upper limit value (Ro) of the assist gradient (R) at the detected vehicle velocity (V),
wherein the lead-lag compensation is performed in such a manner that the frequency of the end point of the phase lead decreases and the frequency of the start point of the phase lag increases according to the increase of the vehicle velocity; and
a correction amount of the output of the motor (10) is varied according to the variation of the assist gradient (R).
